{#def provider, extra="" #}
{#
  OAuth provider button. Used on the auth signup/signin tabs to render
  the white-card "Continue with X" buttons next to the email/password
  form.

  ``provider`` is "google" or "github". The label text and the embedded
  ``auth.OauthIcon`` brand glyph are picked from that.

  The ``oauth-btn`` class hook on the rendered button is load-bearing:
  ``static/auth.js`` finds every OAuth button across the page via
  ``document.querySelectorAll('.oauth-btn')`` to enable/disable and fade them
  as a group during an OAuth flow. The ``oauth-btn-spinner`` span sits (hidden)
  in front of the brand glyph; auth.js reveals it on the button the user
  clicked so there is immediate "something is happening" feedback while the
  browser round-trip runs. ``hidden`` MUST live on this plain wrapper span, not
  on the Spinner component itself -- Spinner renders its own ``inline-block``
  display utility, which is emitted after ``.hidden`` in the compiled CSS and
  would override ``display:none``, leaving the spinner visible at rest (mirrors
  the PermissionsForm hidden-spinner pattern).

  ``extra`` is for one-off layout shims (``mb-2`` to space buttons in a
  vertical stack).
#}
{%- set _label = {"google": "Continue with Google", "github": "Continue with GitHub"}[provider] -%}
<button data-oauth="{{ provider }}"
        class="oauth-btn w-full py-2 px-3 bg-surface-primary border border-default rounded-lg type-body cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-center gap-2 text-primary hover:bg-fill-hover {{ extra }}">
  <span class="oauth-btn-spinner hidden"><Spinner size="sm" /></span><auth.OauthIcon :provider="provider" /> {{ _label }}
</button>
